```julia
function count_model_rows(df_cars::DataFrame)
    return groupby(df_cars, :model) |> g -> length(g)
end
```

This function uses the `groupby` function from the DataFrames.jl package to group the data by the `:model` column and then applies a lambda function to each group that counts the number of rows in the group using `length`. The result is a Series where each element corresponds to the count for a specific model.
